    <text xml:id="t1">
        <body xml:id="t1-body">
            <pb n="1" facs="#rb059a" xml:id="t1-body-pb1"/>            
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place" ref="#ANZ" key="ANZ">Anzac</name>
                    <lb/>
                    <date when="1915-12-05">5 Dec 1915</date>
                </dateline>
                <lb/>
                <lb/>
                <salute>My darling child:</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>I am sending
                <lb/>
                you a little Christmas
                <lb/>
                card, which I hope you
                <lb/>
                will like. It is a
                <lb/>
                little late, but I only
                <lb/>
                had it made a few
                <lb/>
                days ago. Mummy
                <lb/>
                will tell you how it
                <lb/>
                was made.
            </p>
            <p>
                I had all sorts of
                <lb/>
                good reports about you &amp;
                <lb/>
                it makes me very happy
                <lb/>
                to know that I have such
                <lb/>
                an industrious little
                
                <pb n="2" facs="#rb059b" xml:id="t1-body-x3-pb1"/>
                
                daughter who is getting
                <lb/>
                on so well with her
                <lb/>
                lessons.
            </p>
            <p>
                What do you think
                <lb/>
                I saw in the trenches last
                <lb/>
                night! A little frog!
                <lb/>
                I was going along and I
                <lb/>
                saw something black hop
                <lb/>
                so I flashed my light &amp;
                <lb/>
                there was a dear little
                <lb/>
                frog, and his eyes did
                <lb/>
                sparkle so. I picked
                <lb/>
                him up, and he was
                <lb/>
                so cold, and I put him
                <lb/>
                where he would nto get
                <lb/>
                trodden on.            
            </p>
            <p>
                One of the men
                <lb/>
                found a tortoise the other
                <lb/>
                day, such a big one, about
                
                <pb n="3" facs="#rb059c" xml:id="t1-body-x5-pb1"/>
                
                half the size of old Jeremy.
                <lb/>
                He is living now in a
                <lb/>
                dugout, and always tries
                <lb/>
                to get hear the fire           
            </p>
            <p>
                I have not had a
                <lb/>
                letter from you for a
                <lb/>
                long time, but I am
                <lb/>
                expecting one any time
                <lb/>
                now.
            </p>
            <p>
                We had a lot of
                <lb/>
                snow here the other day
                <lb/>
                &amp; it was very cold, but
                <lb/>
                now it is warmer but
                <lb/>
                very muddy.                
            </p>
            <p>
                I hope you had a
                <lb/>
                happy Christmas &amp; that I
                <lb/>
                shall be back to spend
                
                <pb n="4" facs="#rb059d" xml:id="t1-body-x8-pb1"/>
                
                the next one with you.
            </p>
            <p>Be a good little girl
                <lb/>
                always &amp; look after
                <lb/>
                mummy</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>With lots of love
                    <lb/>
                    &amp; humbugs from
                    <lb/>
                    your affectionate <hi rend="u">father</hi></salute>
            </closer>
            <postscript><p>Remember me to Come.</p></postscript>            
        </body>
    </text>
